All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was fixed:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

**Root cause:** The loop condition was `i < items.length - 1`, which stopped one iteration early — skipping the last element entirely.

**Fix:** Changed to `i < items.length` so the loop runs through the full array.

```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

